      .product-point-info
        %h3 Handwoven by Peruvian Artisans
        %p Each strap is handwoven by artisans in Peru. The artisans apply traditional weaving techniques that have been passed down for generations. Most of the artisans are women who work from home with their children playing nearby.
    .product-point
      .product-point-icon
        = image_tag "http://placehold.it/150x150"
      .product-point-info
        %h3 Made with Sustainable & Fair Employment Practices
        %p All of our straps are made according to fair trade guidelines. The artisans earn a living wage, have a safe working environment, and are not subject to workplace pollutants or toxins. There is no child labor.
    .product-point
      .product-point-icon
        = image_tag "http://placehold.it/150x150"
      .product-point-info
        %h3 No Two Straps Are Alike
        %p Each guitar strap is as unique as the person that made it. We offer ten patterns, but the patterns have slight variations due to the hand-crafted process. The personality of the artisan comes through making each strap one of a kind.
    .product-point
      .product-point-icon
        = image_tag "http://placehold.it/150x150"
      .product-point-info
        %h3 Beautiful, Peruvian Fabrics
        %p Unique and distinct as your sound, these skillfully constructed straps stand out from the crowd. While some straps attempt to recreate patterns in factories, these straps are truly authentic.

